Earlier this month, the DA laid charges of corruption against President Jacob Zuma following the release of the state capture report. JOHANNESBURG - The Democratic Alliance (DA) says it has received written confirmation from the Hawks, indicating that they will be investigating corruption charges against President Jacob Zuma. The party's Mabine Seabe says they ve been contacted by the head of the serious commercial crimes unit, who s confirmed that the Hawks will be meeting with the president later this week. Earlier this month, the DA laid charges of corruption against President Zuma over the Public Protector's state of capture report. He says this is a step in the right direction, but they ll be keeping a close eye on the investigation. It s a welcomed step in the right direction and fight against corruption and state capture. But it s not the final step, an investigation must still take place. And if it s found that there is criminal activity in this matter, then the National Prosecuting Authority has a duty to act. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)